<div id="review_746090376" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/746090376" />
    <a title="Hannah" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2411388-hannah"><img alt="Hannah" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1272561978p2/2411388.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/746090376?book_show_action=true">Oct 21, 2013</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Hannah" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Hannah" href="/user/show/2411388-hannah">Hannah</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2411388-hannah?shelf=2013-reads">2013-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2411388-hannah?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2411388-hannah?shelf=biography">biography</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer746090376" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10215974862249052542"><b>Rating Clarification: 4.5 Stars</b><br/><br/>Rating not based on the actual writing per se (it is clear from the often times non-focused and badly edited narrative that Jenna Miscavige Hill is <u>not</u> a professional writer), but on her story about growing up in the <s>wacked-out cult</s> religion of Scientology as the niece of current leader Dave Miscavige from age two until she finally <s>escaped</s> left around age 21.<br/><br/>Kudos to her for speaking up and speaking out. I wish her and her family well in her new life among the &quot;Wog</span>
  <span id="freeText10215974862249052542" style="display:none"><b>Rating Clarification: 4.5 Stars</b><br /><br />Rating not based on the actual writing per se (it is clear from the often times non-focused and badly edited narrative that Jenna Miscavige Hill is <u>not</u> a professional writer), but on her story about growing up in the <s>wacked-out cult</s> religion of Scientology as the niece of current leader Dave Miscavige from age two until she finally <s>escaped</s> left around age 21.<br /><br />Kudos to her for speaking up and speaking out. I wish her and her family well in her new life among the "Wogs".<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="10215974862249052542" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
