<div id="review_2404633523" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2404633523" />
    <a title="Katie B" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/49444196-katie-b"><img alt="Katie B" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1469412116p2/49444196.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2404633523?book_show_action=true">May 28, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Katie B" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Katie B" href="/user/show/49444196-katie-b">Katie B</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/17369296-beyond-belief">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49444196-katie-b?shelf=nonfiction">nonfiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49444196-katie-b?shelf=biography">biography</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49444196-katie-b?shelf=memoir">memoir</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49444196-katie-b?shelf=read-in-2018">read-in-2018</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/49444196-katie-b?shelf=religion">religion</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2404633523" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12479818415454673356">Jenna Miscavige Hill was a third generation Scientologist who left the church in 2005. She is the niece of the current leader of the Church of Scientology, David Miscavige. In this memoir, Jenna shares her experiences growing up in the church and being left to essentially fend for herself as her parents jobs within the organization were priority number one. Jenna talks about her time as a Sea Org member and what ultimately led to her deciding to leave the church.<br/><br/>I thought I knew quite a lot abou</span>
  <span id="freeText12479818415454673356" style="display:none">Jenna Miscavige Hill was a third generation Scientologist who left the church in 2005. She is the niece of the current leader of the Church of Scientology, David Miscavige. In this memoir, Jenna shares her experiences growing up in the church and being left to essentially fend for herself as her parents jobs within the organization were priority number one. Jenna talks about her time as a Sea Org member and what ultimately led to her deciding to leave the church.<br /><br />I thought I knew quite a lot about Scientology before reading, but this book actually provided even more insight. Jenna goes into great detail the different processes children have to go thru when learning about Scientology. A few times the detail got to be a little too much and I was slightly bored but overall it was fascinating to read about all the bizarre stuff one has to do in order to "clear the planet". <br /><br />Even though Jenna is the niece of David Miscavige her experiences with him are pretty limited as she wasn't around him very much, and the same goes for most of her family members. I think she was more than fair when talking about how he was nice to her when she did see him, but as she got older she could see he was controlling and manipulative behind the scenes. What I found heartbreaking was her aunt Shelly, of "where's Shelly" fame, seemed to be kind and protective of Jenna until all of a sudden she wasn't. I tried my best to be non-judgmental but it was difficult at times when you see adults caring more about the church than a child. I really applaud Jenna for having the courage to leave and find happiness on the outside.<br /><br />Would definitely recommend as a good read if you want to learn more about Scientology as Jenna provides a unique perspective as being raised in the church and having relatives high up in the organization. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12479818415454673356" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


